The paper is clearly related to information retrieval (IR), which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a statistically principled method for determining the "true" distribution, which suggests that it may be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to derive a new family of ranking models, which suggests that it may be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and databases (cs.DB).
